{"word":"H8438 - תֹּולָע - tôwlâʻ - to-law' - Crimson","slug":"H8438","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">תֹּולָע</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>tôwlâʻ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>to-law'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Crimson"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05DC;&#x05E2;&#x05EA;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05DC;&#x05E2;&#x05EA;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05DC;&#x05E2;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05DC;&#x05E2; - to&#x0302;la&#x0302;&#x201B;  to&#x0302;le&#x0302;&#x201B;a&#x0302;h  to&#x0302;la&#x201B;ath  to&#x0302;la&#x201B;ath</b> - <i>to-law', to-lay-aw', (3,4) to-lah'-ath</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H3216\">H3216</a>; a <i>maggot</i> (as <i>voracious</i>); specifically (often with ellipsis of <a href=\"#/H8144\">H8144</a>) the crimson <i>grub</i>, but used only (in this connection) of the color from it, and cloths dyed therewith: - crimson, scarlet, worm."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4459\">H4459</a>, <a href=\"#/H4973\">H4973</a>, <a href=\"#/H8439\">H8439</a>, <a href=\"#/H8440\">H8440</a>, <a href=\"#/H8529\">H8529</a>, <a href=\"#/H8530\">H8530</a>"}]}